    title: "RAG Isn't Dead. The Lazy Way You're Doing It Is",
    excerpt: "'RAG is dead' is the hot take of 2026, fueled by long context and agents. The truth: naive chunk-and-retrieve is dying. Retrieval itself is fine.",
    category: "Tooling",
